{"questionId":"9076521","questionHtml":"<p>Monochromatic light of wavelength λ in air is incident normally on a thin film of refractive index <em>n</em>. The film is surrounded by air. The intensity of the reflected light is a minimum. What is a possible thickness of the film?</p>\n<p>A. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{\\lambda }{{4n}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>λ</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{3\\lambda }}{{4n}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mi>λ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{\\lambda }{n}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>λ</mi>\n    <mi>n</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{5\\lambda }}{{4n}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mi>λ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076521","referenceCode":"18M.1.HL.TZ1.27","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Monochromatic light of wavelength λ in air is incident normally on a thin film of refractive index n. The film is surrounded by air. The intensity of the reflected light is a minim","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"27","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.3 – Interference","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}